
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gamemoded` yek daemon (service) ast ke be shoma komak mikonad system-e khod ra baraye bazi beینه (optimize) konid. Vaghti bazi ra shoru mikonid, `gamemoded` be soorat otomatik CPU governor ra be 'performance' taghir midehad, i/o priority ra behtar mikonad, va script-haye digari ke baraye behtar kardan performance-e bazi neveshte shode-and ra ejra mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gamemoded -s`  --> 📊 Status: Namayesh vaziyat-e fa'al ya gheir fa'al budan-e gamemoded.
    🔹 `gamemoded -r`  --> 🔄 Request: Egera-ye dastoor be soorate dasti
    🔹 `gamemoded -d`  --> 💀 Kill: Paak kardane service gamemode

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gamemoded -s

    🔹 Namayesh vaziyat-e gamemoded. Agar bazi fa'al bashad, "active" va agar na bashad "inactive" neshon midehad.

    $ gamemoded -r

    🔹 Egera-ye gamemoded be soorate dasti. In agar gamemoded be soorate otomatik shoru nashavad mofeed ast.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gamemoded -s
    active

    🔹 In neshan midehad ke gamemoded alan fa'al ast va system baraye bazi beینه shode ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gamemoded` command is a daemon (service) that helps you optimize your system for gaming. When you start a game, `gamemoded` automatically changes the CPU governor to 'performance', improves I/O priority, and executes other scripts written to improve gaming performance.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gamemoded -s`  --> 📊 Status: Displays whether gamemoded is currently active or inactive.
    🔹 `gamemoded -r`  --> 🔄 Request: Manually trigger gamemoded to activate.
    🔹 `gamemoded -d`  --> 💀 Kill: Stop the Gamemode service

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gamemoded -s

    🔹 Shows the status of gamemoded.  If a game is active, it will show "active", otherwise it will show "inactive".

    $ gamemoded -r

    🔹 Manually triggers gamemoded to activate.  This is useful if gamemoded doesn't start automatically.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gamemoded -s
    active

    🔹 This indicates that gamemoded is currently active and the system is optimized for gaming.
